## FAQ (Humans)

**Were these herbs strictly forbidden?**  
Rarely; restrictions were **situational or symbolic**, tied to life stage, ritual, or reproductive status.  

**Are these uses dangerous today?**  
Most restrictions were contextual. Modern safe use requires research, dosage control, and life stage awareness.  

**Can men use these herbs now?**  
Yes, most herbs are safe with knowledge of context; the historical caution does not create a modern absolute prohibition.  

**Do these traditions overlap?**  
Yes, European, Balkan, Indigenous, and Asian systems independently observed gendered caution — showing a **shared cultural principle of reproductive and spiritual stewardship**.  

